  <prompt>
    Build `DateExtractorHandler` — a pure-deterministic `IToolHandler` implementation per
    FR-17 that performs date normalization + relative-date resolution from raw text.
    Examples: "next quarter" → ISO 8601 date (start of next calendar quarter); "Q4 2026"
    → 2026-10-01; "March 15" → 2026-03-15 (current year inferred); "2026-03-15" → passthrough.
    NO LLM call. NO Azure OpenAI dependency. Pure C# regex + `DateTime` arithmetic +
    optional `Microsoft.Recognizers.Text.DateTime` (justify if added; size delta tracked).

    Handler registers via auto-discovery per task 100's contract — implements `IToolHandler`;
    `HandlerId = "DateExtractorHandler"`; lives in `Services/Ai/Handlers/DateExtractorHandler.cs`;
    no manual DI line. Requires a corresponding `sprk_analysistool` Dataverse row with
    `sprk_handlerclass = "DateExtractorHandler"` + `sprk_configuration` JSON specifying
    optional `referenceDate`, `defaultTimezone`, `outputFormat` (ISO 8601 default).

    Configurable behavior per FR-17 acceptance: handler accepts optional
    `sprk_configuration` JSON from the tool row; deterministic with the same input +
    same config → same output every time. Telemetry per ADR-015 logs handler name,
    execution outcome, timestamp only.

    Tests: contract test (registered, discoverable, metadata valid) + positive cases
    (relative-date phrases + ISO passthrough + Q-notation) + error cases (malformed
    input, ambiguous-without-reference-date) + config-driven test (referenceDate change
    shifts "next quarter" output).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with .NET 8 + deterministic algorithm experience. Familiar with
    `DateTime` arithmetic, regex, ISO 8601, calendar quarter math, timezone handling.
    Comfortable writing handlers that produce identical output for identical input.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `DateExtractorHandler.cs` implemented in `Services/Ai/Handlers/`; auto-discovered;
    `sprk_analysistool` row exists with `sprk_handlerclass = "DateExtractorHandler"` +
    `AvailableInContexts` set per usage intent (Playbook by default); unit tests pass
    covering positive + error + config-driven cases; ZERO LLM/Azure-OpenAI dependencies
    in handler code; BFF publish-size delta ≤+0.5 MB; `code-review` + `adr-check` green.
  </goal>

