  <context>
    <background>
      `DateExtractorHandler` is one of 8 typed handlers the R6 platform data model
      anticipates but only stubs in code today. It is pure-deterministic — relative-date
      phrase ("next quarter", "EOQ", "in 30 days") + reference date → canonical ISO 8601
      output. No LLM needed, so latency is sub-millisecond and unit tests are stable.

      Use case: legal calendaring (deadlines), invoice due-date normalization, contract
      term expiry calc. Configurable `referenceDate` lets playbooks anchor relative dates
      to a non-"now" baseline (e.g., contract execution date).
    </background>
