    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read every file in &lt;inputs&gt; and &lt;knowledge&gt;. Specifically extract from
      `HandlerRegistrationConventions.md` the 4-point contract; from `GenericAnalysisHandler.cs`
      the implementation shape; from `TypedToolHandlerTestFixture` (created by task 100)
      the shared mocks + helpers.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Design Handler Surface">
      Define: `HandlerId = "DateExtractorHandler"`; `Metadata` with semver version,
      description "Pure-deterministic date normalization + relative-date resolution";
      `SupportedToolTypes` includes appropriate enum; `ConfigSchema` JSON-Schema Draft 07
      with `referenceDate`, `defaultTimezone`, `outputFormat` fields. NO `IOpenAiClient`
      dependency in the constructor.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Handler">
      Create `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/DateExtractorHandler.cs`.
      Implement `Validate(...)` (validates config + input text non-empty). Implement
      `ExecuteAsync(...)`: parses input text for date patterns (regex for ISO/US/EU
      formats + relative phrases); resolves relative dates against `referenceDate` (or
      `DateTimeOffset.UtcNow` default); emits structured `ToolResult` with extracted dates.
      Telemetry per ADR-015.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Author Unit Tests">
      Create `tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/Services/Ai/Handlers/DateExtractorHandlerTests.cs`
      using `TypedToolHandlerTestFixture` from task 100. Cover: (a) contract test (copy
      `HandlerContractTestTemplate`); (b) positive cases — "next quarter", "Q4 2026",
      "March 15", "2026-03-15", "in 30 days"; (c) error cases — empty input, unparseable
      input; (d) config-driven test — same input with different `referenceDate` produces
      different output deterministically; (e) telemetry test — `AssertTelemetryRespectsAdr015`.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Seed sprk_analysistool Row">
      Create `infra/dataverse/sprk_analysistool-date-extractor-row.json` with
      `sprk_handlerclass = "DateExtractorHandler"`, `sprk_toolcode = "DATE-EXTRACT@v1"`,
      `sprk_configuration` JSON, `AvailableInContexts = "Playbook"` (default). Deploy
      row to Spaarke Dev via `dataverse-deploy` skill. Capture deployment evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Verify Build + Tests">
      Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` and
      `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "DateExtractorHandler"`. Both
      must pass. Auto-discovery verification test must show `DateExtractorHandler`
      registered.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify BFF Publish-Size Delta">
      Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/`.
      Measure compressed output. Report absolute size + diff vs prior baseline in task
      notes. Per-task target ≤+0.5 MB.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through every &lt;acceptance-criterion&gt; below and record evidence in task
